        <prompt>What was the significance of the "Coushatta Massacre"?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Murder of Republican officials to regain white Democratic control</option>
            <option letter="b">Labor dispute resolution</option>
            <option letter="c">Religious conflict</option>
            <option letter="d">Economic protest</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Coushatta Massacre of 1874 involved the murder of Republican officials in Louisiana, demonstrating violent Democratic efforts to regain political control.</explanation>
