    <question>
        <prompt>What was the purpose of "forty acres and a mule" certificates?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Temporary land grants that were later revoked</option>
            <option letter="b">Permanent property deeds</option>
            <option letter="c">Agricultural training documents</option>
            <option letter="d">Military service rewards</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The "forty acres and a mule" certificates were temporary land grants given to freedmen by Sherman's Special Field Order 15, but were later revoked by President Johnson.</explanation>
